No, setting up this kind of private server is not illegal, and neither is playing on the server.

The server emu's haven't stolen any source code from Blizzard, but is as I said, just emulating a server.
Not everything on these servers work, but that's a price you have to pay for playing the game for free.

Also, the game is available on Fileplanet for free download with 10 trial days on Blizzard servers.
Download it, patch it and play as much as you like!
http://www.fileplanet.com/163517/160000/fileinfo/World-of-Warcraft---Trial-Client

Setting these servers up is not a hard task and anyone could do it.
It's just about having a tiny ounce of knowledge.
Go get the files somewhere else if the links here are broken.
Google it!

All of this info is available for anyone, so just try to do your homework next time guys!
